                                "start": 9.556,
                                "stop": 33.853,
                                "byte_start": 130008,
                                "byte_stop": 227184,
                                "text": "This case raises a narrow issue of a statutory construction, it involves the question whether the Railroad Commission of Texas in regulate a narrow segment of what is known as Piggyback Service transportation of freight on a partly on a railroad flatcar and partly being hold by a motor carrier in a continuous movement."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 33.853,
                                "stop": 45.828,
                                "byte_start": 227184,
                                "byte_stop": 275145,
                                "text": "The issue blows down to whether when it is the services performed by an interstate rail carrier and the movement itself is entirely within the state of Texas."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 45.828,
                                "stop": 59.455,
                                "byte_start": 275145,
                                "byte_stop": 329688,
                                "text": "Whether the portion of the movement that has provided by trucks and be regulated by Texas and it turns on whether that portion of the movement is considered transportation provided by a rail carrier or by a motor carrier."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 59.455,
                                "stop": 73.716,
                                "byte_start": 329688,
                                "byte_stop": 386635,
                                "text": "And for reason stated in an opinion filed with the Clerk, we conclude that in as much as equipment is entirely own by the railroad at the time and it is a real carrier within the meaning of the statue, that it is a rail carrier transportation."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 73.716,
                                "stop": 83.244,
                                "byte_start": 386635,
                                "byte_stop": 424774,
                                "text": "And therefore an exemption for this portion of the movement ordered by the Interstate Commerce Commission deprives the State of the Texas of the power to regulate this portion."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 83.244,
                                "stop": 88.9,
                                "byte_start": 424774,
                                "byte_stop": 447448,
                                "text": "And we therefore reverse the judgment of the Court of Appeals for the Fifth Circuit which it held to the contrary."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 88.9,
                                "stop": 90.958,
                                "byte_start": 447448,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The opinion is unanimous."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
